  "text": "ReviewsTop Stories Here are my picks for the best iPad cases available now. Image: Cult of Mac You unwrapped a shiny new iPad for Christmas or Hanukkah — congratulations! — and now you need a case for it. I’ve tested a bunch of these and have recommendations for the best iPad cases. These protect your computer from life’s little mishaps. But you can also get an iPad case with a built-in keyboard and trackpad to upgrade your table to a ultralight laptop.This post contains affiliate links. Cult of Mac may earn a commission when you use our links to buy items. A good iPad case should shield your tablet from damage while also acting as a stand for when you’re on the go. And it shouldn‘t add too much bulk. An Apple Pencil holder is a plus. OtterBox Statement Series Studio “Statement Series Studio provides protection and versatility both on and off the job,” says the case-maker.Photo: OtterBox OtterBox is known for excellent cases, and its Statement Series Studio is one of the best I’ve ever used. It includes an adjustable stand and removable front flap, but was still designed to add minimal weight. There’s an innovative sliding Apple Pencil holder, too. In my review of this case, I called it “a brilliant balance of protection and portability.” Buy it from: Amazon 13-inch iPad Air 11-inch iPad Air Protection + portability OtterBox Statement Studio Series Case for iPad 5.0 This iPad Air case (also available for iPad Pro models) delivers ample protection for people who don't take their tablets on adventures. Pros:Protective without being bulkyIncludes kickstand and Apple Pencil slotRemovable front cover Cons:Not compatible with Thunderbolt cables Pitaka MagEZ Folio 2 Pitaka‘s origami-style kickstand is a standout feature.Photo: Pitaka Those wanting the best minimalist iPad case need look no farther than the Pitaka MagEZ Folio 2. It clings magnetically to your tablet, protecting the screen and back from scratches. And the front cover flips around to become an origami-style stand. And don’t overlook the Apple Pencil holder. As I noted in my review, “My M4 iPad Pro still feels thin and super-portable, even in the case.” Buy from: Amazon 13-inch iPad Pro or Air Best minimalist iPad case Pitaka MagEZ Folio 2 4.5 The very slim Pitaka MagEZ Folio 2 clings magnetically to your tablet, protecting the screen and back from scratches. Pros:Very slim and lightweightStand works in portrait an landscape modesApple Pencil holder Cons:Kickstand doesn’t work well in lap Honorable mentions: DodoCase English Bridle Leather iPad Case Mageasy Lift Standing \u0026 Folding Folio iPad Case SwitchEasy Origami Protective Case Best iPad keyboard cases Make your iPad even more useful by upgrading it into a a slim and light notebook computer with a keyboard case. Apple Magic Keyboard for iPad The latest Magic Keyboard for iPad Pro version packs some big upgrades.Photo: Apple With its cool cantilever design, the Apple Magic Keyboard is a standout accessory. And it’s the only iPad keyboard that adds a USB-C charging port to the computer. It attaches magnetically which makes it easy to remove. My review of the case praises the improvements in the latest version, like a glass trackpad and a row of function keys. Buy from: Amazon 11-inch iPad Pro 13-inch iPad Pro iPad 10 Best iPad keyboard case Apple iPad Magic Keyboard Case for iPad Pro 5.0 With its cool cantilever design, the Apple Magic Keyboard is a standout accessory. And it’s the only iPad keyboard that adds a USB-C charging port to the computer.  Pros:Gorgeous designAdd USB-C charging portEasy to remove Logitech Combo Touch Logitech Combo Touch is one of the best iPad keyboard cases.Photo: Logitech Those looking for an iPad keyboard case that focuses more on protecting the tablet should consider the Logitech Combo Touch. It comes in two sections so the keyboard flap can be removed while leaving the iPad in a wrap-around case. And the case portion includes a kickstand. Buy it from: Amazon 13-inch iPad 